<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Download</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/style.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <%- include('partials/nav.ejs') %>
    <main class="download-container">
      <h1>Download Our App</h1>
      <p>Download our mobile app to manage your bike rentals on the go!</p>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/Mohammed12des/Bicycle-Rental-System/archive/refs/heads/main.zip"
        class="btn primary-btn"
        >Download Now</a
      >
      <h1>Setup and Installation</h1>

      <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
      <p>
        To get started with the <strong>Bicycle Rental System</strong>, you’ll
        need:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Node.js</strong> and <strong>npm</strong>:
          <a href="https://nodejs.org">Download Node.js</a>
          <ul>
            <li>
              This installs <code>npm</code> as well, which you’ll use to manage
              dependencies.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Step 1: Clone the Repository</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Open your terminal</strong>.</li>
        <li>
          <strong>Clone the repo</strong> by running:
          <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/Mohammed12des/Bicycle-Rental-System.git</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Navigate to the project directory</strong>:
          <pre><code>cd Bicycle-Rental-System</code></pre>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Step 2: Install Dependencies</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Install backend dependencies</strong>:
          <pre><code>npm install</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Navigate to the <code>client</code> directory</strong> (if
          there's a React frontend):
          <pre><code>cd client</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Install frontend dependencies</strong>:
          <pre><code>npm install</code></pre>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Step 3: Running the Project</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Start the backend</strong>:
          <ul>
            <li>
              Go back to the root directory:
              <pre><code>cd ..</code></pre>
            </li>
            <li>
              Run the backend server:
              <pre><code>npm start</code></pre>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Start the frontend (if applicable)</strong>:
          <ul>
            <li>
              If there's a <code>client</code> directory, start the React app:
              <pre><code>cd client
  npm start</code></pre>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p>That’s it! Now you can start building on the project.</p>

      <hr />
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
